Esval, a Valparaiso, Chile-based
water utility, plans to sell as much as $46 million of
inflation-linked bonds due in either 10 or 20 years, according
to a person familiar with the sale.  Esval will sell the bonds on April 24, the person said.  Esval is majority owned by the Ontario Teachersâ€™ Pension
